Description: Body sherd of black-figured pottery closed vase, perhaps amphora; exterior: from left, right hand extended to right; possibly part of one or two draped figures with added red on garment(s), to left.
Curator's comments: While the clay is light for Attic, the style does point in that direction.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0073) (Phase 1)
